There are two exits in a bus with 100 seats: First exit is located beside seat number 1. Second exit is located beside seat number 100. Seats are arranged in a straight line from 
1 to 100, 100 with equal spacing between any 2 adjacent seats. A passenger prefers to choose the nearest exit while leaving the bus.
Determine the exit taken by passenger sitting on seat X. For each test case, output LEFT if the passenger chooses the exit beside seat 1, RIGHT otherwise.




#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
	int X;
	scanf("%d",&X);
	if(X>=1&&X<=50) {
	    printf("Left");
	} else {
	    printf("Right");
	}

}
